In Debian/Ubuntu

Install dependencies

{{{
}}}

Install packages

{{{
sudo aptitude install python-m2crypto python-openssl python-django
}}}
{{{
sudo pip install django-uni-form
}}}

or

Download the application

From git:
{{{
git clone https://github.com/bennomadic/django-webid-provider.git
}}}
From release tarball:
{{{
wget http://github.com/bennomadic/django-webid-provider/tarball/master)
tar -xvzf django-webid-provider-0.1.tar.gz
cd django-webid-provider-0.1
}}}

Create a virtualenv

{{{
virtualenv --no-site-packages django-webid-env
}}}

Install dependencies

{{{
source django-webid-env/bin/activate
pip install -E django-webid-env -r examples/example_webid_provider/requirements/external_apps.txt
}}}

Modify settings (settings_local.py) according to your installation:
{{{
...
}}}


